`%t2 = sub i8 %y, %t1`
Here, `Op0` is `%y` and `Op1` is `%t1` (the select). `Op0` is not zero.

The transformation is `sub y, (select c, x, -x)` -> `add y, (select c, -x, x)`.
This is `sub y, z` -> `add y, (-z)`.
The code at line 2250 is `CreateAdd(NegOp1, Op0)`. This is `(-z) + y`, which is correct.

